WEBVTT

00:01.935 --> 00:03.370
- Her parents are turning the
backyard into a movie theater,

00:03.436 --> 00:05.638
and everyone's getting
their own personal snack bar.

00:05.705 --> 00:07.374
- All our friends
are gonna be there.

00:07.440 --> 00:08.975
- Can we go? Please?
- Please?

00:09.042 --> 00:10.276
- Absolutely not.

00:10.343 --> 00:12.712
No sleepovers
until you get your grades up.

00:12.779 --> 00:14.914
- Mom, why? That's so unfair.

00:14.981 --> 00:17.217
- No, it's not.
Besides, you know how I feel

00:17.283 --> 00:18.985
about Cindy and her weird
parents.

00:19.052 --> 00:20.920
- They're not weird.
They're cool.

00:20.987 --> 00:23.656
- The answer is no. Come on.
Inside.

00:32.232 --> 00:34.234
- Hello there, ladies.

00:34.300 --> 00:35.502
- It's dad!

00:35.568 --> 00:37.303
- ♪ Burn, baby, burn ♪

00:37.370 --> 00:39.406
[The Trammps' "Disco Inferno"
playing]

00:39.472 --> 00:40.907
- A disco ball!

00:40.974 --> 00:42.675
- This is so cool!

00:42.742 --> 00:46.246
- Ah-ah-ah-ah. Come on.
Off my couch. Off my couch.

00:46.312 --> 00:47.614
Cecil, what is all this?

00:47.680 --> 00:49.516
- It's a disco party.

00:49.582 --> 00:51.785
- Wh-why?
- Why not?

00:51.851 --> 00:53.620
I thought this family could use
a little fun right now.

00:53.686 --> 00:56.022
Check it out, girls.

00:56.089 --> 00:58.358
- Oh, my God.
Is that a karaoke machine?

00:58.425 --> 00:59.993
- Is this bike for me?
- Yep.

01:00.059 --> 01:01.661
And you've got
two other presents there.

01:01.728 --> 01:02.829
You can open them now.

01:02.896 --> 01:04.397
And I've got one other
big surprise.

01:04.464 --> 01:05.465
It's in the other room.

01:05.532 --> 01:07.233
- Cecil, we can't afford
all this.

01:07.300 --> 01:08.935
- Hold that thought,
Mrs. Walsh.

01:09.002 --> 01:11.237
Next dance is for you.

01:11.304 --> 01:14.774
- Oh, it's the unicorn hoodie
I've been telling you about!

01:14.841 --> 01:17.477
- No way.
Is this what I think it is?

01:17.544 --> 01:19.646
Yes! I got a mini tablet!

01:19.712 --> 01:21.114
- Those are some
awesome presents.

01:21.181 --> 01:23.516
- Okay, Karlie, Amanda,
sit on the couch.

01:23.583 --> 01:27.120
Close your eyes.
Here comes the big surprise.

01:27.187 --> 01:29.989
- ♪ The heat was on ♪

01:30.056 --> 01:31.157
- Ready?

01:31.224 --> 01:32.425
- Yeah.
- Yep.

01:32.492 --> 01:35.962
- Are your eyes closed
really tight?

01:36.029 --> 01:37.630
- Yup.
- [giggles]

01:37.697 --> 01:39.466
- ♪ That is when my spark
got hot ♪

01:39.532 --> 01:41.034
♪ I heard somebody say ♪

01:41.100 --> 01:43.102
[gunshots]
- [screaming]

01:43.169 --> 01:45.038
- ♪ Disco inferno ♪

01:45.104 --> 01:46.806
- Why are you doing this?

01:46.873 --> 01:48.241
- ♪ Burn that mother down ♪

01:48.308 --> 01:50.176
♪ Burn, baby, burn ♪

01:50.243 --> 01:52.078
♪ Disco inferno ♪

01:52.145 --> 01:53.646
♪ Burn, baby, burn ♪

01:53.713 --> 01:55.682
♪ Burn that mother down ♪

01:55.748 --> 01:57.350
♪ Burn, baby, burn ♪

01:57.417 --> 01:59.419
[vocalizing]

01:59.486 --> 02:02.088
♪ Burn, baby, burn ♪

02:02.155 --> 02:05.091
[dramatic music]

02:05.158 --> 02:07.961
♪ ♪

02:11.131 --> 02:13.032
- Have you seen my phone?

02:13.099 --> 02:14.200
I can't find it anywhere,

02:14.267 --> 02:16.202
and I don't want
to be late for court.

02:16.269 --> 02:18.271
- Between the headboard
or maybe the nightstand?

02:18.338 --> 02:20.507
- Looked there already.
- Well, babe, I don't know.

02:20.573 --> 02:22.008
I'm late for work too,
and I can't find

02:22.075 --> 02:24.043
Anais' spelling worksheet
anywhere.

02:25.845 --> 02:27.547
- Never mind. Found it.

02:29.349 --> 02:31.518
- Mommy, I had an accident.

02:31.584 --> 02:32.986
- Anais, you're soaking wet.

02:33.052 --> 02:34.120
- Sorry.

02:34.187 --> 02:36.923
- Go run and get a new shirt.
Quick.

02:36.990 --> 02:39.292
Of all the days for Renee
to call in sick.

02:39.359 --> 02:41.394
- It's the third time
she's bailed this month.

02:41.461 --> 02:43.396
What nanny does that?
- I am so over it.

02:43.463 --> 02:45.732
We need to have
a serious talk with her.

02:45.798 --> 02:49.135
- Hello, hello. Help is here.

02:49.202 --> 02:52.639
- Mom, thank you for coming.
You're a life saver.

02:52.705 --> 02:54.841
- Not a problem.

02:54.908 --> 02:56.209
How are you, Charlotte?

02:56.276 --> 02:57.710
- Good. Running a little late.

02:57.777 --> 03:00.046
- Hang on a sec. Come here.

03:00.113 --> 03:01.548
Let me see.

03:03.249 --> 03:05.985
Like I said, boy.
You're hanging low.

03:07.554 --> 03:11.057
- Mama B.
- Oh, look at my angel.

03:11.124 --> 03:12.659
Why are you wet?

03:12.725 --> 03:14.661
- I spilled milk.

03:14.727 --> 03:16.095
- You let her go to school
like that?

03:16.162 --> 03:17.530
- No, she's supposed
to be changing.

03:17.597 --> 03:20.199
Anais, clean shirt. Hurry up.

03:20.266 --> 03:23.403
- I really need to go.
Thanks again, Susan.

03:23.469 --> 03:24.637
- Wait, no, no.
Mom, that can wait.

03:24.704 --> 03:25.738
Anais is late.

03:25.805 --> 03:28.541
- No, it cannot.
I never start my day

03:28.608 --> 03:30.710
with a dirty kitchen,
and neither should you.

03:30.777 --> 03:33.813
- Ah-ah-ah-ah. I got this. Go.

03:33.880 --> 03:36.182
- All right.

03:36.249 --> 03:38.952
Love you.
- Love you too.

03:41.688 --> 03:44.424
- No way. I got a mini tablet!

03:44.490 --> 03:46.392
- Those are some
pretty awesome presents.

03:46.459 --> 03:48.861
- Okay, Karlie, Amanda,
sit on the couch.

03:48.928 --> 03:50.630
Close your eyes.

03:50.697 --> 03:54.467
Here comes the big surprise.
Ready?

03:54.534 --> 03:55.802
- Yeah.
- Yep.

03:55.868 --> 03:58.137
- Are your eye closed
really tight?

03:58.204 --> 04:01.741
- Yeah.
- Yep.

04:01.808 --> 04:05.211
[gunshots]
- [screaming]

04:05.278 --> 04:07.080
Why are you doing this?
[gunshot]

04:09.515 --> 04:12.385
- Okay, 6:00 a.m. this morning,
Fairfield, Connecticut.

04:12.452 --> 04:14.821
Next door neighbor goes
to the house of Ellen Walsh

04:14.887 --> 04:16.356
to go for their daily walk,

04:16.422 --> 04:17.991
knocks on the door,
and there's no answer.

04:18.057 --> 04:20.627
She peeks through the window,
and she finds the bodies

04:20.693 --> 04:24.230
of Ellen and her two daughters,
Amanda and Karlie.

04:24.297 --> 04:27.033
All three were killed
by Cecil Walsh.

04:27.100 --> 04:28.101
He's the husband of Ellen.

04:28.167 --> 04:29.535
They were married
three years ago.

04:29.602 --> 04:31.237
The daughters are from
a previous relationship.

04:31.304 --> 04:34.007
- Our fugitive is a family
annihilator with one DUI

04:34.073 --> 04:35.775
and no history of violence.

04:35.842 --> 04:37.710
The room was set up
like a disco.

04:37.777 --> 04:40.647
Lights. Mirror balls.
The whole nine yards.

04:40.713 --> 04:43.383
- And he's in costume.

04:43.449 --> 04:44.984
Torn wrapping paper
on the floor.

04:45.051 --> 04:46.519
The girls opening gifts.

04:46.586 --> 04:47.754
Maybe this was his weird way

04:47.820 --> 04:49.822
of giving them
one last happy moment.

04:49.889 --> 04:52.425
- Or a way to distract them
before he attacks.

04:52.492 --> 04:55.695
This is classic
psychopathic behavior.

04:55.762 --> 04:58.898
He's calm and detached
as he executes his family,

04:58.965 --> 05:00.867
showing no hesitation
or remorse.

05:00.933 --> 05:03.469
- What activated him?
- Money could be the motive.

05:03.536 --> 05:05.872
Meaning the lack of it.
He was deep in debt.

05:05.938 --> 05:08.841
Unpaid credit card bills,
house in foreclosure,

05:08.908 --> 05:11.144
and both cars
on the verge of being repoed.

05:11.210 --> 05:12.812
And it looks like
he was recently let go

05:12.879 --> 05:14.781
from his engineering job
at a firm

05:14.847 --> 05:16.015
in Hartford, Connecticut.

05:16.082 --> 05:18.351
His last paycheck
was a month ago.

05:18.418 --> 05:19.686
He was the sole breadwinner.

05:19.752 --> 05:21.287
Ellen has no
employment history.

05:21.354 --> 05:22.822
- Okay, so maybe his ego

05:22.889 --> 05:24.190
and male pride
got the better of him.

05:24.257 --> 05:26.059
Didn't want his family
to think less of him

05:26.125 --> 05:27.860
for not being able
to provide financially.

05:27.927 --> 05:31.064
So he killed them before
they could learn the truth.

05:31.130 --> 05:33.332
- Why don't you head
to Cecil's last job.

05:33.399 --> 05:36.903
See why he was fired.
Barnes, dig into the victims.

05:36.969 --> 05:39.972
The rest of us are gonna
head to the crime scene.

05:40.039 --> 05:42.975
[suspenseful music]

05:43.042 --> 05:49.982
♪ ♪

05:50.049 --> 05:52.985
[indistinct chatter]

05:53.052 --> 05:56.089
[siren wailing]

05:59.092 --> 06:00.793
We'll check the room
with the bodies.

06:00.860 --> 06:02.695
You check the rest
of the house.

06:07.366 --> 06:11.237
[somber music]

06:11.304 --> 06:14.340
- [sighs]
Cecil really went all out.

06:15.808 --> 06:18.544
- He planned this meticulously.

06:21.214 --> 06:23.082
How old were the girls?

06:23.149 --> 06:25.084
- 11 and 12.

06:25.151 --> 06:29.822
♪ ♪

06:29.889 --> 06:31.691
- Take a look
at these pictures.

06:31.758 --> 06:34.093
Cecil isn't in any of 'em.

06:35.995 --> 06:37.563
- Weird.
- Mm-hmm.

06:39.398 --> 06:41.534
It's almost like it's not even
a part of this family.

06:41.601 --> 06:43.336
- When did his financial
problems start?

06:43.402 --> 06:44.937
- About a year ago.

06:45.004 --> 06:46.806
- They were married in 2018.

06:46.873 --> 06:48.407
Based on the age of the girls,

06:48.474 --> 06:52.011
I'm assuming these photos were
taken in the last few years.

06:52.078 --> 06:54.347
- Are you saying Cecil
was alienating himself?

06:54.413 --> 06:57.650
- From his family and before
his financial troubles.

06:57.717 --> 06:59.685
- Hey, guys, I have something
to show you.

06:59.752 --> 07:02.588
[suspenseful music]

07:02.655 --> 07:05.424
♪ ♪

07:05.491 --> 07:07.460
- Cecil's man-cave?

07:07.527 --> 07:08.861
- I don't think so.

07:08.928 --> 07:10.863
It looks like they were having
marital issues,

07:10.930 --> 07:12.765
and there's no sign of them
sharing the master bedroom.

07:12.832 --> 07:15.168
All his clothes and his
belongings are in this room.

07:15.234 --> 07:17.203
I mean, there was--
there was this.

07:17.270 --> 07:19.839
I found this box locked
under the bed.

07:21.808 --> 07:23.176
- Pine cones?

07:23.242 --> 07:25.044
- They were preserved
with some sort of a laminate.

07:25.111 --> 07:27.947
And they're all numbered.

07:28.014 --> 07:29.649
Total of 35.

07:29.715 --> 07:33.452
- How bizarre.
Why is he hoarding pine cones?

07:33.519 --> 07:35.988
- Could have some kind of
sentimental value.

07:36.055 --> 07:39.091
That's why he's keeping them
in a case under his bed.

07:39.158 --> 07:40.960
- I remember
making bird feeders with these

07:41.027 --> 07:42.228
in elementary school.

07:42.295 --> 07:44.430
Could be some kind
of childhood trauma.

07:44.497 --> 07:45.965
- Could be.

07:47.700 --> 07:50.169
Could be
some kind of weird fetish.

07:52.138 --> 07:54.173
Let's go talk to the neighbor.

07:55.942 --> 07:59.045
- Cecil had been with the firm
about 10 years.

07:59.111 --> 08:01.547
I can't believe he would do
something so awful.

08:01.614 --> 08:03.082
Those poor girls.

08:03.149 --> 08:05.885
- Had you noticed a change
in his behavior recently?

08:05.952 --> 08:07.053
- About a month ago,

08:07.119 --> 08:09.155
he started acting distant,
kind of strange.

08:09.222 --> 08:10.756
- Strange how?

08:10.823 --> 08:12.491
- Like his mind was elsewhere.

08:12.558 --> 08:14.393
Suddenly it was a struggle
for him to finish projects,

08:14.460 --> 08:15.828
and when he finally did,

08:15.895 --> 08:17.663
they were riddled
with mistakes.

08:17.730 --> 08:19.966
It was out of character.

08:20.032 --> 08:22.001
- And did he mention
what was bothering him?

08:22.068 --> 08:24.136
Problems at home? His family?

08:24.203 --> 08:27.006
- No, he just apologized
and corrected the mistakes.

08:27.073 --> 08:28.741
The revisions were
always pitch perfect

08:28.808 --> 08:30.910
just like his work
had been before.

08:30.977 --> 08:33.446
- And did he have a history
of volatility on the job?

08:33.512 --> 08:34.714
- Not at all.

08:34.780 --> 08:36.749
He was a friendly,
mild-mannered guy.

08:36.816 --> 08:39.452
A real team player
and a very hard worker.

08:39.518 --> 08:41.454
Essentially,
he was the perfect employee

08:41.520 --> 08:43.856
and an asset to the firm.

08:43.923 --> 08:45.558
- So why did you fire him?

08:46.859 --> 08:48.294
- I didn't.

08:48.361 --> 08:50.129
I actually offered him
a promotion

08:50.196 --> 08:52.231
with a very substantial raise
about a month ago,

08:52.298 --> 08:56.035
but he turned it all down,
and he resigned.

08:56.102 --> 08:58.037
- Cecil was heavily in debt.

08:58.104 --> 08:59.939
It doesn't make sense that
he'd walk away from the answers

09:00.006 --> 09:01.674
to all his financial troubles.

09:01.741 --> 09:03.743
- Well, the only explanation
he gave me was,

09:03.809 --> 09:07.246
"Money can't fix the pain.
Nothing can."

09:08.915 --> 09:10.283
- I feel terrible.

09:10.349 --> 09:12.285
Ellen and I power-walked
around the neighborhood

09:12.351 --> 09:14.320
every morning,
6:00 a.m. on the dot.

09:14.387 --> 09:15.688
When I didn't see her outside,

09:15.755 --> 09:17.657
I got a sinking feeling
in my stomach.

09:17.723 --> 09:19.592
It's just so shocking.

09:19.659 --> 09:23.095
- Did you notice anything off
between Cecil and his family?

09:23.162 --> 09:24.931
- Nothing between him
and the little girls,

09:24.997 --> 09:27.633
but Cecil and Ellen's marriage
was on its last leg.

09:27.700 --> 09:28.801
- How so?

09:28.868 --> 09:30.303
- I don't think he ever
really loved her.

09:30.369 --> 09:31.837
I mean, he just seemed
to be going through the motions

09:31.904 --> 09:33.272
of being a husband.

09:33.339 --> 09:34.340
- And what about Ellen?

09:34.407 --> 09:35.708
- She was ga-ga about him,

09:35.775 --> 09:38.344
but she told me he'd become
increasingly distant.

09:38.411 --> 09:40.179
Started giving her
the cold shoulder.

09:40.246 --> 09:41.847
I mean,
they were barely speaking.

09:41.914 --> 09:44.083
- And did they ever mention
anything about divorce?

09:44.150 --> 09:46.385
- Poor Ellen was still trying
to make the marriage work.

09:46.452 --> 09:49.322
And then last week,
Cecil started leaving the house

09:49.388 --> 09:51.824
at odd hours,
and Ellen got suspicious.

09:51.891 --> 09:53.926
She started following him
in her car.

09:55.328 --> 09:58.531
- And that's her car there?
- Yeah.

09:58.597 --> 10:01.934
- Only saved entries are home
and Cecil's office.

10:02.001 --> 10:03.602
- She doesn't know her way
to either one?

10:03.669 --> 10:04.737
- Well, I do the same thing.

10:04.804 --> 10:05.972
Store the entries of the places

10:06.038 --> 10:08.541
I go to the most
so I can check traffic.

10:08.607 --> 10:10.409
Let's look at
the most recent destinations.

10:10.476 --> 10:12.411
- There's half a dozen
entries there.

10:12.478 --> 10:13.813
- They're in
chronological order,

10:13.879 --> 10:16.048
so this one at the top
is the most recent.

10:16.115 --> 10:18.317
- That's also the only address
not in Connecticut.

10:18.384 --> 10:21.420
- Hold on. Hold on.
What is that? 780 Wilson Way.

10:21.487 --> 10:23.255
- Yeah, in Brooklyn.

10:24.423 --> 10:27.226
- It's St. Bertrand's
Catholic Church.

10:27.293 --> 10:29.595
- There are plenty of Catholic
churches around here.

10:29.662 --> 10:31.497
Why is Cecil going
all the way to Brooklyn?

10:31.564 --> 10:33.532
- I don't know,
but it's all we got.

10:33.599 --> 10:35.034
- Want us to check it out?

10:35.101 --> 10:37.470
- Sounds good.
I'll finish up here.

10:37.536 --> 10:40.473
[ominous music]

10:40.539 --> 10:47.580
♪ ♪

11:07.867 --> 11:10.269
- Tell me, what is weighing
on your heart, my son?

11:10.336 --> 11:12.371
What sins would you like
to confess?

11:12.438 --> 11:14.607
- Father,
why should I even bother?

11:14.673 --> 11:16.642
It won't make any difference.

11:16.709 --> 11:19.512
- Well, the Bible tells us
if we confess our sins,

11:19.578 --> 11:21.647
he is faithful and just
to forgive our sins

11:21.714 --> 11:23.682
and cleanse us
from all unrighteousness.

11:23.749 --> 11:26.318
- Some souls are too rotten
to be cleansed.

11:26.385 --> 11:28.187
- God is merciful.

11:28.254 --> 11:31.190
He doesn't sit in judgment
of those who seek his grace.

11:31.257 --> 11:35.494
- It isn't his judgment
we should be worried about.

11:35.561 --> 11:38.297
At least not here on Earth.

11:38.364 --> 11:41.400
- Well, whatever is
troubling you, we can fix it.

11:41.467 --> 11:45.071
All it takes is faith
and forgiveness.

11:45.137 --> 11:46.439
- Not for me.

11:46.505 --> 11:49.708
- [choking]

11:49.775 --> 11:56.816
♪ ♪

12:14.834 --> 12:17.470
- We've got one victim,
Father Adam Jones.

12:17.536 --> 12:19.939
Church secretary found him
about an hour ago.

12:20.005 --> 12:21.173
At first she thought
it was a heart attack

12:21.240 --> 12:24.310
until she saw ligature marks
around his neck.

12:24.376 --> 12:28.447
Looks like it could have been
some sort of a belt or a strap.

12:28.514 --> 12:30.015
- We sure this is Cecil?

12:30.082 --> 12:31.951
- No one saw him,
but we did find

12:32.017 --> 12:33.486
his fingerprints
in the confessional booth,

12:33.552 --> 12:35.521
which matched his DUI file.

12:35.588 --> 12:37.923
- Using a belt
instead of his hands,

12:37.990 --> 12:40.126
that would create more pain.

12:40.192 --> 12:43.062
For some reason, Cecil wanted
the priest to suffer.

12:43.129 --> 12:45.231
- Pretty brazen doing it
in broad daylight.

12:45.297 --> 12:46.398
- Not really.

12:46.465 --> 12:47.967
Cecil's been here before,

12:48.033 --> 12:49.835
so he probably knew this place
would be empty during the day.

12:49.902 --> 12:51.470
- So what does a disco theme
have to do

12:51.537 --> 12:52.872
with a religious murder?

12:52.938 --> 12:55.841
- That's a good question.
The disco theme is an odd one.

12:55.908 --> 12:58.344
- And how does his family
play into all of this?

12:59.879 --> 13:02.414
- Cecil doesn't fit
the profile.

13:02.481 --> 13:04.617
A family annihilator
is a narcissist.

13:04.683 --> 13:06.485
They kill their family
because they think

13:06.552 --> 13:09.121
they can't survive without 'em.

13:09.188 --> 13:13.125
Cecil is a narcissist,
but for whatever reason

13:13.192 --> 13:15.461
he's chosen
not to kill himself yet.

13:16.662 --> 13:18.597
- There's something else
he needs to do first.

13:18.664 --> 13:19.965
- Exactly.

13:20.032 --> 13:22.368
- Cecil's boss said
he was in pain,

13:22.434 --> 13:24.637
which is why he didn't take
the promotion at work.

13:24.703 --> 13:28.541
So maybe killing a priest is
his way of lashing out at God.

13:28.607 --> 13:30.109
- The secretary says

13:30.176 --> 13:33.245
that Father Jones
only worked here for two years.

13:33.312 --> 13:35.814
He spent his entire career
in DC.

13:35.881 --> 13:37.316
I looked him up,
and he was assigned

13:37.383 --> 13:39.118
to three different churches,
but he mostly just worked

13:39.185 --> 13:40.653
at various charities.

13:40.719 --> 13:42.888
- Any connections to Cecil?
- No.

13:42.955 --> 13:44.690
But speaking of Cecil,
I did find this.

13:44.757 --> 13:46.625
Nine parking tickets
to his car,

13:46.692 --> 13:50.329
all issued on expired meters
outside a wine shop in Queens,

13:50.396 --> 13:51.797
all issued within
the last month.

13:51.864 --> 13:53.999
- Maybe he's trying to drink
his problems away?

13:54.066 --> 13:55.601
- Or maybe Father Jones

13:55.668 --> 13:58.204
wasn't the only person
Cecil's been stalking.

13:59.605 --> 14:01.540
- All right, you three
check out the neighborhood

14:01.607 --> 14:03.609
for witnesses
and security cams.

14:03.676 --> 14:05.678
Kris and I will check out
the wine shop.

14:05.744 --> 14:07.213
See if it means anything.

14:07.279 --> 14:08.847
[suspenseful music]

14:08.914 --> 14:11.784
- That guy?
Yeah, he was, uh, here a lot.

14:11.850 --> 14:13.586
Always badgering
one of my employees.

14:13.652 --> 14:15.321
- Which one?
- Nora Bryant.

14:15.387 --> 14:16.689
- Any idea what sparked
the harassment?

14:16.755 --> 14:18.324
- No clue--
she said they were friends,

14:18.390 --> 14:19.925
but she didn't want
to talk about it,

14:19.992 --> 14:22.194
so I didn't push.

14:22.261 --> 14:23.495
- His name is Cecil Walsh.

14:23.562 --> 14:25.531
When's the last time
you saw him?

14:25.598 --> 14:27.933
- Last time Nora worked.

14:28.000 --> 14:29.868
- When was that?
- Last week.

14:29.935 --> 14:32.204
She quit after the guy
showed up again.

14:33.639 --> 14:36.442
This guy really killed
four people?

14:36.508 --> 14:39.044
- So far, yeah.
- The world's messed up.

14:39.111 --> 14:40.512
I just thought
he was an old flame,

14:40.579 --> 14:43.115
or maybe Nora owed him money
or something.

14:43.182 --> 14:45.684
- We're gonna need the address
where Nora's working now.

14:45.751 --> 14:48.320
- And a photo of Nora,
if you have one.

14:48.387 --> 14:49.888
- Of course.

14:49.955 --> 14:56.795
♪ ♪

14:56.862 --> 14:59.298
- Any luck with the
neighborhood canvas?

14:59.365 --> 15:00.766
- Negative. No cameras.

15:00.833 --> 15:02.234
And nobody saw Cecil arriving

15:02.301 --> 15:04.003
at the church
or leaving, either.

15:04.069 --> 15:05.304
- We've got a lead.

15:05.371 --> 15:08.507
I think a Nora Bryant
is Cecil's next target.

15:08.574 --> 15:09.875
- We've been trying
to reach her,

15:09.942 --> 15:12.177
but there's no answer
on her cell or her landline.

15:12.244 --> 15:14.380
- What's the connection
between Nora and Cecil?

15:14.446 --> 15:16.348
- They were friends.
They had a falling out.

15:16.415 --> 15:18.317
- What was that about?
- I'm not sure.

15:18.384 --> 15:19.985
But whatever it was
was bad enough

15:20.052 --> 15:22.187
that Nora's been
trying to avoid him.

15:22.254 --> 15:23.856
- We're heading to Nora's house
in Queens.

15:23.922 --> 15:25.557
You guys head to her new job.

15:25.624 --> 15:27.626
It's a mini-storage
in Brooklyn.

15:27.693 --> 15:30.663
I just sent you the address
and Nora's photo.

15:30.729 --> 15:31.964
- Copy.

15:32.031 --> 15:34.867
- Three bubble wrap.
We got that.

15:34.933 --> 15:37.536
14 of these vacuum bags.
We should double check those.

15:37.603 --> 15:38.971
That's enough, right?

15:39.038 --> 15:40.773
It's just your winter wardrobe.

15:42.474 --> 15:45.044
- Nora?

15:45.110 --> 15:46.912
- Cecil, what are you
doing here?

15:46.979 --> 15:48.280
How did you even find me?

15:48.347 --> 15:49.915
- I--I just wanna talk.

15:49.982 --> 15:51.350
- No, no.
There's nothing to talk about.

15:51.417 --> 15:53.252
Please just go.

15:53.319 --> 15:56.922
- Is there a problem?
- Mind your business.

15:56.989 --> 15:59.525
- I've seen your face.
You're on the news.

15:59.591 --> 16:02.127
- He's lying.
- No, I saw him.

16:02.194 --> 16:03.662
They say he killed
his whole family.

16:03.729 --> 16:05.264
- What?
- I'm telling you that's him.

16:05.331 --> 16:06.632
- Put the phone down.

16:06.699 --> 16:09.268
- No.
- I said put it down!

16:09.335 --> 16:10.836
[gunshot]
[Nora gasps]

16:10.903 --> 16:12.971
- Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

16:13.038 --> 16:15.040
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.
Please, please, please.

16:15.107 --> 16:17.276
- Calm down. Calm down.

16:17.343 --> 16:20.112
- Please don't hurt me, Cecil.
Please just let me go.

16:20.179 --> 16:23.415
- I'm not going to hurt you.
I just want to talk.

16:23.482 --> 16:24.917
Just not here, okay?

16:24.983 --> 16:26.352
- No, I don't want
to go anywhere.

16:26.418 --> 16:29.355
[tense music]

16:29.421 --> 16:31.190
♪ ♪

16:31.256 --> 16:33.092
- That's Cecil's Lexus.
Heads up.

16:34.326 --> 16:35.494
- I don't wanna go with you.
- No, no.

16:35.561 --> 16:37.196
We're leaving right now.

16:37.262 --> 16:38.931
- It's the girl from the photo.

16:40.666 --> 16:43.435
- Gun!
[gunshots]

16:43.502 --> 16:46.171
- Go, go! Run, Nora.

16:46.238 --> 16:48.707
- He's heading out the back.
I'll go 'round.

16:48.774 --> 16:50.175
- FBI!

16:50.242 --> 16:52.010
- Man down!

16:52.077 --> 16:59.118
♪ ♪

17:17.903 --> 17:20.639
- What happened?
- He had a gun.

17:20.706 --> 17:22.808
He yanked me out of my car,
and he hit me.

17:22.875 --> 17:25.711
- He's not inside.
- Did he have a woman with him?

17:25.778 --> 17:27.946
- Yes--
he forced her into my car,

17:28.013 --> 17:30.249
and he took my car.
He took my car.

17:30.315 --> 17:31.717
- Okay, ma'am,
I need you to calm down.

17:31.784 --> 17:33.218
We're going to find your car.

17:40.058 --> 17:41.794
- FBI. Anybody home?

17:41.860 --> 17:43.462
[suspenseful music]

17:43.529 --> 17:44.897
Hello?

17:44.963 --> 17:46.899
[phone ringing]
- I don't see anybody.

17:48.400 --> 17:52.438
Ortiz, we're at
Nora Bryant's house.

17:52.504 --> 17:54.373
Pretty sure she's not here.

17:54.440 --> 17:57.009
- Cecil has her.
He showed up at her new job.

17:57.075 --> 17:58.110
He shot the manager,

17:58.177 --> 18:00.212
then he carjacked a lady
to get away.

18:00.279 --> 18:01.380
PD's on the hunt.

18:01.447 --> 18:02.948
- So he kidnapped Nora.

18:03.015 --> 18:04.850
- We're going through
security footage now.

18:04.917 --> 18:06.785
I'm sending it to your tablet.

18:08.821 --> 18:10.789
- Cecil shoots the manager
without hesitating,

18:10.856 --> 18:13.125
but the way he handles
Nora is different.

18:13.192 --> 18:15.794
- He's gentle, comforting.

18:15.861 --> 18:17.930
His hand even shakes
when he holds the gun at her.

18:17.996 --> 18:20.065
The manager said
that Cecil told Nora

18:20.132 --> 18:21.533
that he just wanted to talk.

18:21.600 --> 18:23.535
- But he still grabbed her
at gunpoint, shaking or not.

18:23.602 --> 18:25.103
So what's going on here?

18:25.170 --> 18:27.072
- I'm not sure,
but if he has her,

18:27.139 --> 18:29.608
then they can have that talk.

18:29.675 --> 18:31.510
If Nora's smart,
she'll play along.

18:31.577 --> 18:33.879
I gotta go.

18:33.946 --> 18:37.950
Excuse me, sir. FBI.

18:38.016 --> 18:40.252
You live here?
- Yes.

18:40.319 --> 18:42.354
- Do you know Nora Bryant?

18:42.421 --> 18:44.456
- Yeah, she's my fiancée.

18:44.523 --> 18:46.024
Why, what's going on?

18:47.659 --> 18:49.228
From the moment I met Cecil,

18:49.294 --> 18:50.696
I knew something
was off about him.

18:50.762 --> 18:51.964
- And why is that?

18:52.030 --> 18:53.198
- He just--
he gave off bad vibes.

18:53.265 --> 18:55.467
He seemed like a phony.

18:55.534 --> 18:57.069
I told Nora to stop
hanging out with him,

18:57.135 --> 18:58.403
but she didn't listen.

18:58.470 --> 19:01.874
- Why do you think she didn't
take your advice?

19:01.940 --> 19:04.810
- Nora sympathizes with people.

19:04.877 --> 19:06.245
Her parents died
when she was young,

19:06.311 --> 19:07.846
and she doesn't
have any siblings,

19:07.913 --> 19:12.251
so she tends to overcompensate
with kindness and acceptance.

19:12.317 --> 19:13.719
It's one of the reasons
I love her so much.

19:13.785 --> 19:15.654
She tries to only see
the best in people.

19:15.721 --> 19:17.523
- And how did she
and Cecil meet?

19:17.589 --> 19:20.025
- He came into her store
about a month ago.

19:20.092 --> 19:23.195
Said he was a wine lover.
I guess they hit it off.

19:23.262 --> 19:26.832
The very next day, he texted
her wanting to grab coffee.

19:26.899 --> 19:28.867
Then they--they started
going out for drinks,

19:28.934 --> 19:30.636
dinners here and there,

19:30.702 --> 19:33.138
meeting up for museum visits.

19:33.205 --> 19:35.641
- So they were friends
at one point?

19:35.707 --> 19:37.009
- Yes.

19:37.075 --> 19:39.912
Yeah, I even went wine tasting
with them once.

19:39.978 --> 19:41.346
She thought he was just lonely

19:41.413 --> 19:43.749
and looking
for people to hang out with.

19:43.815 --> 19:47.753
She was actually protective
of him in this weird way.

19:47.819 --> 19:50.155
- And what caused
the friendship to sour?

19:54.593 --> 19:56.695
- Our engagement.

19:56.762 --> 19:58.897
I popped the question
a couple weeks ago.

19:58.964 --> 20:01.099
Nora told Cecil,
and he flipped out.

20:01.166 --> 20:05.070
He tried to convince her that
I wasn't good enough for her.

20:05.137 --> 20:07.806
And he pushed hard for our
engagement to be called off.

20:07.873 --> 20:09.541
- I'm sure
that didn't sit well.

20:11.543 --> 20:14.446
- Cecil doesn't even know me.
He barely knows Nora.

20:14.513 --> 20:15.581
I was livid.

20:15.647 --> 20:16.915
I called him and I told him
to stop

20:16.982 --> 20:18.951
meddling in our lives
and to stay the hell away.

20:19.017 --> 20:21.920
- And that's when the stalking
and the harassment started?

20:24.156 --> 20:25.891
- Yeah.

20:25.958 --> 20:29.061
♪ ♪

20:29.127 --> 20:31.296
What if that's
what set Cecil off?

20:31.363 --> 20:33.198
What if this is my fault?

20:33.265 --> 20:34.766
- This is not your fault,
Daniel.

20:34.833 --> 20:36.868
- You have to find Nora.
Please.

20:39.438 --> 20:41.573
I can't lose her.

20:44.977 --> 20:47.145
- Help! Somebody help me!
- Nora! Nora!

20:47.212 --> 20:48.547
- Please!

20:48.614 --> 20:51.717
- Calm down. Enough.
It's enough. Really.

20:51.783 --> 20:54.553
- Help!
- It's gonna be okay.

20:54.620 --> 20:56.622
- I just wanna go home. Please.

20:56.688 --> 20:58.490
Please, I won't say anything
to anybody.

20:58.557 --> 21:00.759
Please just let me go home.

21:00.826 --> 21:04.129
- You are home.
This is ours now.

21:05.497 --> 21:06.932
Hey.

21:08.767 --> 21:10.302
It's gonna be okay.

21:12.170 --> 21:13.572
I promise.

21:13.639 --> 21:15.207
[tense music]

21:15.273 --> 21:17.509
- No. No.
- [chuckles] Oh, my God.

21:17.576 --> 21:19.911
- [sobbing]

21:19.978 --> 21:22.381
- I have so much planned
for us,

21:22.447 --> 21:25.751
but you need to eat first.
- I'm not hungry.

21:25.817 --> 21:28.787
- Just try. I'll be back soon.

21:28.854 --> 21:31.890
- Wait, where--
where are you going?

21:31.957 --> 21:34.292
[sobbing]
Cecil, let me out of here!

21:35.794 --> 21:40.032
Come on. Let me go.
[sobs]

21:40.098 --> 21:41.667
- These are from
Nora's home computer.

21:41.733 --> 21:44.102
She and Cecil having dinner
at the museum.

21:44.169 --> 21:45.771
Even singing karaoke together.

21:45.837 --> 21:47.239
- They look happy.

21:47.305 --> 21:49.207
- Yeah, they were until
Nora told Cecil

21:49.274 --> 21:50.909
she was engaged to Daniel.

21:50.976 --> 21:52.177
- Well, why would he be upset?

21:52.244 --> 21:53.578
They weren't dating.
They were just friends.

21:53.645 --> 21:55.080
- In Nora's mind, maybe.

21:55.147 --> 21:56.948
I think Cecil
was in love with her.

21:57.015 --> 21:58.684
Could be why he started
distancing himself

21:58.750 --> 21:59.851
from his family.

21:59.918 --> 22:01.753
- And the source
of their marital problems.

22:01.820 --> 22:03.722
- When Cecil finds out
Nora's engaged,

22:03.789 --> 22:07.125
he goes into a jealous rage,
so he kills his family,

22:07.192 --> 22:10.162
Kidnaps Nora to have her
all to himself.

22:10.228 --> 22:11.997
- Not the best dating strategy.

22:12.064 --> 22:15.367
- The problem is the priest.
I don't see where he fits in.

22:15.434 --> 22:17.069
- Also the timeline.

22:17.135 --> 22:18.637
Cecil found out about
the engagement, what,

22:18.704 --> 22:20.072
two weeks ago?

22:20.138 --> 22:21.740
So why'd he wait
to make his move?

22:21.807 --> 22:23.475
- Well, maybe there was
another trigger.

22:23.542 --> 22:27.245
- Maybe, but if Cecil's plan
is to remove all obstacles

22:27.312 --> 22:28.513
to him and Nora,

22:28.580 --> 22:31.183
that puts Daniel
in danger, right?

22:32.884 --> 22:34.686
We have agents at their house?

22:34.753 --> 22:36.588
- Yeah, and PD.

22:39.691 --> 22:40.659
- All right.

22:40.726 --> 22:43.562
Any other targets
we can think of?

22:43.628 --> 22:45.163
- None that I can think of.

22:45.230 --> 22:47.799
- What about tip line, BOLOs?

22:47.866 --> 22:49.000
- All quiet.

22:51.937 --> 22:53.772
- [exhales]

22:58.376 --> 23:01.313
[suspenseful music]

23:01.379 --> 23:04.449
♪ ♪

23:04.516 --> 23:06.518
- Hi, Eli.

23:06.585 --> 23:07.819
- Who the hell are you?

23:07.886 --> 23:09.755
- Meg sent me.

23:09.821 --> 23:11.957
[both grunting]

23:12.023 --> 23:13.825
- What--what are you--
[grunts]

23:13.892 --> 23:20.832
♪ ♪

23:20.899 --> 23:22.968
- You should have loved her.

23:23.034 --> 23:25.203
- [grunts]

23:25.270 --> 23:27.606
- Why didn't you love her?

23:27.672 --> 23:29.441
You should have loved her.

23:33.111 --> 23:36.615
You Should have loved her!

23:36.681 --> 23:38.517
- Hey, hey!
What the hell's going on?

23:38.583 --> 23:40.252
- I'm calling the cops.

23:48.994 --> 23:50.595
- Yeah, you better run!

23:58.003 --> 23:59.271
- Fingerprints found
at your home match to this man.

23:59.337 --> 24:00.672
Cecil Walsh.

24:00.739 --> 24:02.274
- Is he the person
who attacked you?

24:02.340 --> 24:04.509
- Yeah, that's the bastard.
- You know him?

24:04.576 --> 24:06.611
- Never seen him
before last night.

24:06.678 --> 24:07.913
- You were very fortunate.

24:07.979 --> 24:09.981
He's killed four people
in the last two days.

24:10.048 --> 24:12.551
- I wasn't scared of that punk.

24:12.617 --> 24:14.219
- He also kidnapped
a young woman

24:14.286 --> 24:16.221
by the name of Nora Bryant.

24:16.288 --> 24:19.591
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.
He took Nora?

24:21.493 --> 24:23.028
- You know her?

24:24.462 --> 24:26.498
- Technically, she's my niece.

24:26.565 --> 24:28.400
My sister and her husband
adopted her

24:28.466 --> 24:29.901
when she was a baby.

24:29.968 --> 24:32.470
Nine years later, they--they
both died in a car accident,

24:32.537 --> 24:33.805
so I was stuck with her.

24:33.872 --> 24:35.740
- What do you mean stuck?
- I never wanted kids.

24:35.807 --> 24:38.910
What was I going to do?
Let the kid go into the system?

24:38.977 --> 24:40.412
So I took her in.

24:40.478 --> 24:42.113
Not that she ever
appreciated it.

24:42.180 --> 24:45.450
- You two weren't close?
- We butted heads a lot.

24:45.517 --> 24:48.386
Never really got along.

24:48.453 --> 24:50.722
When she graduated high school,
she left.

24:50.789 --> 24:52.057
I haven't seen her since.

24:52.123 --> 24:53.692
- Why didn't you get along?

24:55.393 --> 24:57.896
Mr. Bryant, what happened
between the two of you?

24:57.963 --> 25:01.266
[pensive music]

25:01.333 --> 25:06.471
♪ ♪

25:06.538 --> 25:08.039
- Were you abusing her?

25:08.106 --> 25:12.377
- Hell, no. It wasn't that.
- No? What was it?

25:12.444 --> 25:14.546
- Well, I drank too much.

25:16.448 --> 25:20.118
I never once touched her.

25:20.185 --> 25:21.786
I know I wasn't exactly
the best father.

25:21.853 --> 25:25.290
I just, uh, I didn't know how.

25:26.791 --> 25:28.426
I didn't want to
to begin with--

25:28.493 --> 25:29.861
you know what, screw this!

25:29.928 --> 25:32.230
Shouldn't you guys be out there
focused on tracking down

25:32.297 --> 25:34.733
the maniac that put me
in this damn hospital?

25:36.334 --> 25:39.237
- All right, why don't you
help us out with that?

25:39.304 --> 25:41.840
Did Cecil mention anything
about your niece,

25:41.907 --> 25:43.541
where he's holding her,
or anything like that?

25:43.608 --> 25:46.912
- No, he just rambled on
about me not loving her,

25:46.978 --> 25:50.081
which, you know, didn't make
any sense at the time.

25:50.148 --> 25:51.216
[groans]

25:51.283 --> 25:53.585
I guess he was
talking about Nora.

25:53.652 --> 25:55.420
- Anything else?

25:55.487 --> 25:58.123
- Yeah, he said somebody named
Meg sent him to my house.

25:58.189 --> 25:59.557
- And who's Meg?

25:59.624 --> 26:02.961
- Some crackpot named
Megan Taylor's been emailing me

26:03.028 --> 26:06.698
for six weeks now claiming
to be Nora's birth mother.

26:06.765 --> 26:09.701
And me and Nora's relationship
being what it is,

26:09.768 --> 26:11.836
I just deleted 'em and didn't
give 'em another thought.

26:11.903 --> 26:13.405
- And you still have
those emails?

26:13.471 --> 26:17.008
- Yeah, they should be
in my--my trash folder.

26:18.710 --> 26:20.545
- I'm about to send you
some emails.

26:20.612 --> 26:22.914
I need you and Barnes to track
the IP address

26:22.981 --> 26:25.717
from the sender, Megan Taylor.

26:25.784 --> 26:29.254
She might be able to help us
find Nora and Cecil.

26:29.321 --> 26:31.389
- Well, the emails were sent
from an IP address

26:31.456 --> 26:33.591
at this location
to an Eli Bryant.

26:33.658 --> 26:34.893
- Yeah,
the residents are allowed

26:34.960 --> 26:36.428
to use the desktops
in the common room.

26:36.494 --> 26:38.897
- So the woman that sent them
does live here, Megan Taylor?

26:38.964 --> 26:41.599
- She did for six months,
but not anymore.

26:41.666 --> 26:43.668
Meg struggled with addiction
most of her life

26:43.735 --> 26:45.070
but managed to get clean.

26:45.136 --> 26:47.472
Then she relapsed last week.
Missed curfew.

26:47.539 --> 26:50.208
Came back high on meth.
I was forced to kick her out.

26:50.275 --> 26:51.676
- Any idea where she landed?

26:51.743 --> 26:53.878
- Yeah, the county morgue.

26:53.945 --> 26:56.681
One of my other residents told
me she OD'd a few days ago.

26:56.748 --> 27:00.251
- You ever seen Meg
with this guy?

27:00.318 --> 27:02.120
His name's Cecil Walsh.

27:02.187 --> 27:05.390
- Yeah, they were friends.
He's visited her a few times.

27:05.457 --> 27:07.792
The last one right before
I had to kick Meg out.

27:07.859 --> 27:09.294
These are the desktops
they use.

27:09.361 --> 27:11.463
- Did Meg mention anything
to Cecil

27:11.529 --> 27:13.231
about trying
to contact a daughter

27:13.298 --> 27:14.799
she might've put up
for adoption?

27:14.866 --> 27:16.267
- I'm sure she did.

27:16.334 --> 27:18.103
Meg constantly talked about
wanting to reunite

27:18.169 --> 27:20.205
with her baby girl
to anyone who would listen.

27:20.271 --> 27:21.840
- Well, what did she say
about the baby?

27:21.906 --> 27:23.641
- I don't know
if she was telling the truth

27:23.708 --> 27:25.610
or the drugs talking,
but she said that

27:25.677 --> 27:28.313
some Catholic school in DC
called St. Mary's Academy

27:28.380 --> 27:31.049
had stole her kid,
and she was gonna get her back.

27:31.116 --> 27:32.851
- How was she gonna do that?

27:32.917 --> 27:35.020
- Well, she had already located
the adoptive parents

27:35.086 --> 27:36.821
with the help of a nonprofit.

27:36.888 --> 27:39.157
That's probably how she found
this Eli Bryant guy too,

27:39.224 --> 27:40.525
whoever he is.

27:40.592 --> 27:42.060
Thank you, Melissa.

27:42.127 --> 27:43.461
These are all Meg's things.

27:43.528 --> 27:44.996
No one's come to claim them,

27:45.063 --> 27:46.931
and I don't have any contact
info for the next of kin.

27:46.998 --> 27:48.633
So feel free to take it.

27:48.700 --> 27:50.435
I need to go check
on a resident.

27:50.502 --> 27:53.438
- Thanks.
- Thank you.

27:53.505 --> 27:55.874
- Not much in here. Clothes.

27:57.342 --> 27:58.877
Meg and Cecil.

27:58.943 --> 28:02.047
They must be 15, 16 here.

28:02.113 --> 28:04.616
- Meg and Cecil forever.

28:08.153 --> 28:11.990
They weren't just friends.
They were in love.

28:13.792 --> 28:16.895
Cecil and Meg went to the same
school in Upstate New York.

28:16.961 --> 28:19.664
Cecil graduated from there,
but Meg didn't.

28:19.731 --> 28:22.567
Meg graduated
from St. Mary's in DC.

28:22.634 --> 28:23.968
We spoke to them.

28:24.035 --> 28:26.237
Turns out it used to be
a school for unwed mothers.

28:26.304 --> 28:28.440
- They confirm Meg
went there in 1986

28:28.506 --> 28:29.808
when she was
six months pregnant.

28:29.874 --> 28:31.242
- Was Cecil the father?

28:31.309 --> 28:33.945
- Yes, but nobody contacted him
after Meg gave birth.

28:34.012 --> 28:36.681
Instead they just put
baby Nora up for adoption.

28:36.748 --> 28:39.250
- So Cecil does love Nora,
but it's not romantic.

28:39.317 --> 28:41.086
It's because
she's his daughter.

28:41.152 --> 28:42.087
- There's more.

28:42.153 --> 28:44.322
Our priest, Father Jones,

28:44.389 --> 28:46.925
he was on the board
of St. Mary's in the '80s.

28:46.991 --> 28:49.127
He was head of
family placements.

28:49.194 --> 28:52.163
He supervised Nora's adoption.

28:52.230 --> 28:54.999
- I'm confused.
Help me try to break this down.

28:55.066 --> 28:58.169
Six weeks ago,
Meg was clean and sober.

28:58.236 --> 29:00.672
She decides she finally
wants to meet her daughter.

29:00.738 --> 29:02.407
She has her name

29:02.474 --> 29:05.376
and she locates Eli Bryant
through the nonprofit.

29:05.443 --> 29:07.412
- Right, but Eli won't
talk to anyone.

29:07.479 --> 29:08.646
- She finds Cecil.

29:08.713 --> 29:09.881
- We don't know how yet.

29:09.948 --> 29:11.983
- And suddenly Cecil
quits his job

29:12.050 --> 29:14.085
and starts
trying to befriend Nora.

29:14.152 --> 29:16.020
All goes well until
two weeks ago

29:16.087 --> 29:18.723
when Cecil finds out
that Nora is engaged.

29:18.790 --> 29:21.459
- Nora starts avoiding him.
- Cecil starts stalking her.

29:21.526 --> 29:26.197
- And meanwhile, Meg relapses
and dies of an overdose.

29:26.264 --> 29:27.899
And when was that?
- Three days ago,

29:27.966 --> 29:29.767
right before Cecil
murdered his family.

29:29.834 --> 29:32.137
- That's the trigger--
maybe Cecil's plan all along

29:32.203 --> 29:33.872
was to get rid of the family
that he never loved

29:33.938 --> 29:35.940
and replace them with one
that he always wanted.

29:36.007 --> 29:39.744
But Meg's death ruined that
and sent him into a rage.

29:39.811 --> 29:42.213
- And he kills the priest
because he blames him

29:42.280 --> 29:44.082
for giving his daughter away.

29:44.149 --> 29:46.084
- And attacks Eli for being
given the chance

29:46.151 --> 29:50.421
to raise and love Nora,
but drove her away instead.

29:57.362 --> 29:59.397
- When was Nora born?

29:59.464 --> 30:03.568
- September 21, 1986.

30:03.635 --> 30:05.470
- First day of fall.

30:05.537 --> 30:07.605
Those pine cones
that Cecil kept,

30:07.672 --> 30:11.543
how many were there?
- Um, 35.

30:11.609 --> 30:13.611
- One for each year
of Nora's life.

30:13.678 --> 30:14.812
Cecil was honoring the birth

30:14.879 --> 30:15.947
of a daughter
that he never knew

30:16.014 --> 30:17.415
but desperately wanted
to connect with.

30:17.482 --> 30:19.751
- Well, now he has.
- Right.

30:19.817 --> 30:21.152
The question is,

30:21.219 --> 30:24.322
where is this father-daughter
reunion taking place?

30:24.389 --> 30:26.157
[tense music]

30:26.224 --> 30:27.825
- What was Ellen Walsh's
maiden name?

30:27.892 --> 30:29.093
- Cecil's wife?

30:29.160 --> 30:30.328
- Yeah, I just realized

30:30.395 --> 30:32.096
we never ran her
through the property records.

30:32.163 --> 30:34.299
- You know what,
I saw their marriage license

30:34.365 --> 30:36.301
in the file here, hang on.

30:36.367 --> 30:39.537
Cole. Ellen Marie Cole.

30:39.604 --> 30:40.838
- Here we go.

30:40.905 --> 30:42.373
Okay, Ellen inherited

30:42.440 --> 30:43.841
a house from her parents
when they died.

30:43.908 --> 30:45.310
She's the only name
on the deed,

30:45.376 --> 30:46.945
but Cecil paid
the property taxes.

30:47.011 --> 30:49.614
- Where is that?

30:49.681 --> 30:51.482
- In Baldwin on Long Island.

30:51.549 --> 30:53.418
It's probably
where he's holding Nora.

30:53.484 --> 30:55.019
- Let's go.

30:58.656 --> 31:02.193
- That's your mother, Megan.

31:02.260 --> 31:04.495
But everybody called her Meg.

31:04.562 --> 31:06.331
[sentimental music]

31:06.397 --> 31:08.700
- She's pretty.
- Yeah.

31:11.336 --> 31:14.539
- And the day I saw her,
I was head over heels in love,

31:14.606 --> 31:18.176
and she felt the same about me.

31:18.243 --> 31:23.548
I'd never met anyone
as smart and funny and kind.

31:23.615 --> 31:28.186
She had the biggest heart,
just like someone else I know.

31:30.154 --> 31:32.590
When she told me
she was pregnant with you...

31:32.657 --> 31:35.093
[laughs]
I was scared.

31:36.961 --> 31:39.964
But also excited,
and so was your mom.

31:40.031 --> 31:42.267
We were young,
but we didn't care.

31:42.333 --> 31:44.002
We were going to be a family.

31:44.068 --> 31:48.940
♪ ♪

31:49.007 --> 31:51.175
And then they sent her away.

31:52.844 --> 31:55.713
- Who did? Who sent her away?

31:58.783 --> 32:00.218
- Her parents.

32:04.122 --> 32:07.558
- Did they tell you
when I was born?

32:07.625 --> 32:10.795
- No, no.

32:10.862 --> 32:13.865
I knew your mom was due
in September.

32:13.931 --> 32:16.901
So I knew there was a baby
out there that was mine.

32:16.968 --> 32:19.203
I didn't know
if you were a boy or girl.

32:19.270 --> 32:21.572
I didn't even know
where your mother was.

32:23.274 --> 32:27.679
Then a--a couple of weeks ago
out of the blue,

32:27.745 --> 32:30.648
she found me on Facebook.

32:32.917 --> 32:34.819
And I found you.

32:36.487 --> 32:39.957
- I never knew anything
about my birth parents.

32:40.024 --> 32:43.328
Why didn't you just tell me
when we first met?

32:44.796 --> 32:48.966
- I didn't want to scare you.
I--

32:49.033 --> 32:50.968
I wanted you to know me first.

32:57.608 --> 33:02.814
For 35 years, I have prayed
that I would find you,

33:02.880 --> 33:04.615
and it finally happened.

33:04.682 --> 33:08.186
And I have made sure that
no one will stand in our way.

33:08.252 --> 33:12.290
Not my wife and step-kids.
Not your uncle.

33:12.357 --> 33:18.096
No one's ever gonna stop us
from being a family ever again.

33:18.162 --> 33:21.165
I promise.

33:21.232 --> 33:22.934
I love you, Nora.

33:28.773 --> 33:30.041
- Can I give you a hug?

33:30.108 --> 33:37.048
♪ ♪

33:37.115 --> 33:38.950
[lock clicks]

33:41.119 --> 33:43.354
- [sobs]

33:43.421 --> 33:49.260
♪ ♪

33:54.332 --> 33:55.700
- [grunts]
- Ow!

33:57.468 --> 33:58.870
No! Nora!
[gunshot]

33:58.936 --> 34:01.239
- [gasping]

34:01.305 --> 34:03.307
- Are you all right?
Are you okay?

34:03.374 --> 34:06.310
[tense music]

34:06.377 --> 34:08.980
W--wait!

34:09.046 --> 34:10.982
Nora, wait!

34:11.048 --> 34:17.922
♪ ♪

34:32.103 --> 34:34.705
[tense music]

34:34.772 --> 34:37.642
- I was walking in the woods,
and I--I heard a gunshot.

34:37.708 --> 34:39.944
Um, came from that house
right there.

34:40.011 --> 34:43.648
Uh, a woman ran out,
and a man was chasing her.

34:43.714 --> 34:46.184
- Where'd they go?
- Through the backyard there.

34:46.250 --> 34:48.386
- All right.
Well, thank you for your help.

34:48.453 --> 34:51.055
You guys take the path.
We'll cut through the yard.

34:51.122 --> 34:56.861
♪ ♪

34:56.928 --> 34:59.997
- One of them must be shot.
We got blood.

35:02.066 --> 35:04.869
- Nora!

35:04.936 --> 35:06.370
Nora!

35:06.437 --> 35:09.607
We need to work this out
so we can be a family!

35:09.674 --> 35:11.976
That's all I ever wanted!

35:13.678 --> 35:17.482
Nora, stop.
Th--this is my fault.

35:19.617 --> 35:22.019
Please, Nora!

35:24.789 --> 35:26.924
We need to work this out!

35:26.991 --> 35:30.194
Can we do that please, Nora?

35:30.261 --> 35:31.329
Nora?

35:34.832 --> 35:38.069
- We got footprints and blood.

35:38.135 --> 35:45.176
♪ ♪

35:48.513 --> 35:50.348
- [screams]
- No, wait.

35:50.414 --> 35:52.016
- No!
- Wait. Talk to me.

35:52.083 --> 35:53.417
- Cecil--
- Please wait.

35:53.484 --> 35:54.852
- No, I don't want this!

35:54.919 --> 35:59.357
I don't want you in my life.

35:59.423 --> 36:03.528
[sobbing]
- Okay, okay, okay.

36:03.594 --> 36:08.566
Maybe we weren't meant
to be a family here on Earth.

36:08.633 --> 36:12.503
Maybe--maybe the only way
the three of us--

36:12.570 --> 36:17.008
you, me, and Mom--could truly
be together is in heaven.

36:17.074 --> 36:20.545
- No, no. No, no.

36:20.611 --> 36:22.680
- I love you.

36:22.747 --> 36:23.881
- No, no.

36:23.948 --> 36:25.249
- I--I love you so much!
- No!

36:25.316 --> 36:26.918
[gunshot]

36:35.960 --> 36:37.461
- Shots fired. Suspect is down.

36:37.528 --> 36:40.131
We need an ambulance
at 68 Hazel Way,

36:40.197 --> 36:41.966
Baldwin on Long Island.

36:42.033 --> 36:44.969
[solemn music]

36:45.036 --> 36:46.971
♪ ♪

36:47.038 --> 36:51.375
- Nora, deep breaths in, okay?
In and out. In and out.

36:51.442 --> 36:53.744
Can I see the wound?
Okay, an ambulance is coming.

36:53.811 --> 36:55.379
It's going to be
all right, okay?

36:55.446 --> 36:56.881
- Okay.
- Just keep breathing.

36:56.948 --> 37:00.484
In and out. Okay.
- [breathes deeply]

37:00.551 --> 37:01.819
- Well done.

37:01.886 --> 37:04.322
Ambulance is coming.
Just keep breathing.

37:08.826 --> 37:12.096
- Hey, honey.
Dinner will be ready in a few.

37:12.163 --> 37:13.798
- I am starving.

37:13.864 --> 37:15.967
Thank you.
- Mm.

37:16.033 --> 37:18.536
- Hi, baby. I love you.

37:24.375 --> 37:27.211
You okay?
- Not really.

37:27.278 --> 37:30.014
I got another text from Renee.

37:30.081 --> 37:31.616
- She say why she quit?

37:31.682 --> 37:33.784
- Some nonsense about
wanting to go on tour

37:33.851 --> 37:35.019
with her boyfriend.

37:35.086 --> 37:36.887
Her timing really sucks.

37:36.954 --> 37:39.156
- Don't worry about it.
We'll find someone else.

37:39.223 --> 37:41.692
- Sheryll, I'm in the middle
of my first trial

37:41.759 --> 37:43.060
with a huge client.

37:43.127 --> 37:44.929
I don't have the time
or the energy

37:44.996 --> 37:46.998
to start looking
for someone new right now.

37:47.064 --> 37:49.700
- You don't need to find
a new nanny.

37:49.767 --> 37:51.002
You got me right here.

37:51.068 --> 37:52.770
I'm more than happy
to keep helping.

37:52.837 --> 37:54.305
- Not a good idea.

38:01.646 --> 38:04.081
- Baby girl,
let's, uh, go to the market.

38:04.148 --> 38:07.985
I think we need some more flour
for our cookies.

38:08.052 --> 38:09.987
- They're about to argue,
right?

38:10.054 --> 38:12.423
- Ahh.

38:12.490 --> 38:13.758
Come on.

38:17.995 --> 38:21.098
- Why are you so
against my mom helping?

38:21.165 --> 38:23.100
- She cooks,
she does the laundry.

38:23.167 --> 38:24.969
- She drives me crazy.

38:25.036 --> 38:28.773
- Everything I do is wrong.
I coddle Anais too much.

38:28.839 --> 38:30.741
I don't use the right comb
for her hair.

38:30.808 --> 38:32.743
I don't buy
the right hand soap.

38:32.810 --> 38:36.480
And even dinner.
Do you know what she's making?

38:36.547 --> 38:38.449
- That smells like pot roast.

38:38.516 --> 38:39.817
- Exactly.

38:39.884 --> 38:41.719
I told her that I can't eat
red meat right now

38:41.786 --> 38:43.020
because it makes me nauseous.

38:43.087 --> 38:44.321
And her response?

38:44.388 --> 38:46.857
"Oh, that'll pass.
Drink ginger ale."

38:46.924 --> 38:48.526
- She shouldn't have said that,
but--

38:48.592 --> 38:49.694
- There's no but.

38:49.760 --> 38:51.295
Sheryll, are you forgetting

38:51.362 --> 38:52.897
that two years
after our wedding,

38:52.963 --> 38:56.133
your mother still referred
to me as your special friend?

38:56.200 --> 38:58.335
- Okay, I get it.

38:58.402 --> 39:00.738
But she's competent
and she loves Anais.

39:00.805 --> 39:03.240
And she also happens
to be free.

39:03.307 --> 39:05.743
so we can save extra money
and...

39:06.777 --> 39:08.245
Well, this is only temporary.

39:11.048 --> 39:12.683
- Temporary until when?

39:12.750 --> 39:17.388
- Until the baby comes,
then you can take the reins.

39:17.455 --> 39:20.124
- Wait a minute.

39:20.191 --> 39:22.026
Do you think
I'm taking maternity leave

39:22.093 --> 39:24.261
and staying home
after I deliver?

39:24.328 --> 39:26.630
- Yes.

39:26.697 --> 39:29.533
That's what you promised when
we decided to conceive again.

39:29.600 --> 39:31.035
Wait, what's going on here?

39:31.102 --> 39:33.437
Why are you acting like
this wasn't the plan all along?

39:33.504 --> 39:35.573
- That was before
I had a full-time job.

39:35.639 --> 39:37.775
- Yeah, and before you decided
on a whim to go back to work.

39:37.842 --> 39:40.177
You said you wanted to be
a stay-at-home mom.

39:44.014 --> 39:45.816
So what?

39:45.883 --> 39:47.685
You're not taking your leave?

39:50.421 --> 39:54.792
- Why does it have to be me
to have to give up working?

39:54.859 --> 39:56.327
What about you?

39:56.393 --> 40:00.297
Can't you make a sacrifice for
our family and take time off?

40:00.364 --> 40:03.634
[tense music]

40:03.701 --> 40:06.103
- Babe, that wasn't the plan.

40:06.170 --> 40:11.075
- Well, we need a new one then,
'cause this isn't working.

40:11.142 --> 40:18.182
♪ ♪

40:33.164 --> 40:36.100
[dramatic music]

40:36.167 --> 40:43.207
♪ ♪

40:53.217 --> 40:54.919
[wolf howls]
